     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="6"/>
   <p>great benefit and comfort by this worke, if, (after his returne home from the hearing of any godly Lecture or Sermon, where he hath either heard any principle of God his Religion, handled and spoken off: Or else any vertue commended, or vice condem<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ned) he shall turne to that point, and first search it out in the Table, and so then to Read all such Similies in the Booke, as he shall there find, tou<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ching the same point and matter.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>R. C.</signed>
   </closer>
